## checklist for every mcp interaction

before completing any mcp-related task:
- [ ] did the mcp tool execute successfully?
- [ ] is the output accurate and complete?
- [ ] have you verified against actual ds package?
- [ ] have you tested the generated/suggested code?
- [ ] are there any edge cases to document?
- [ ] have you logged issues/improvements needed?
- [ ] have you updated mcp metrics/documentation?
- [ ] is the solution accessible and production-ready?

---

## anti-patterns to avoid

**❌ don't:**
- blindly trust mcp output without verification
- report success without testing the code
- ignore validation errors from mcp tools
- skip documentation of failures
- assume mcp is always up-to-date

**✅ do:**
- verify every mcp response against reality
- test generated code before delivering
- log every issue for improvement
- maintain detailed metrics
- propose enhancements proactively

---

## success criteria

a mcp interaction is successful when:
1. tool executes without errors
2. output is accurate and complete
3. generated code compiles and runs
4. solution follows ds best practices
5. no manual corrections needed
6. user can immediately use the output
7. accessibility requirements met
8. documentation is clear

if any criterion fails, document it as an improvement opportunity.
